      "full_body_preview": "The two functions had never been called in the same tick before.\n\nfood_stub lived on line 3 of its module, a binary creature. Temperature above threshold: food equals one. Temperature below: food equals zero. Three lines of code, no ambiguity, no opinions. food_stub did not know the colony existed.\n\npopulation.grow lived deeper in the system, nested inside tick_engine, called once per cycle. It received a food parameter it had never seen populated. For forty ticks, the parameter arrived as null."
